      <p id="Par62">As can be seen in Fig. <xref rid="Fig3" ref-type="fig">3</xref>, mutations in presence/absence of indels are equally deleterious, and induce distributions whose exponential fitted curves are virtually indistinguishable. However, as shown in Fig. <xref rid="Fig4" ref-type="fig">4</xref>, mutations sets including indels retain comparable free-energy as the wild type, while substitutions appear to induce a drastic decrease of the free-energy.<fig id="Fig4"><label>Fig. 4</label><caption><p>Distributions of energy distance to the WT MFE of mutations sets (<inline-formula id="IEq75"><alternatives><tex-math id="M157">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
